Minimum energy transferred in the form of proton $=-13.6\left(\frac{1}{2^2}-\frac{1}{1^2}\right)=\frac{3}{4} \times 13.6 \mathrm{ev}$.
$\begin{aligned}
& \text { from COE } \frac{1}{2} m v^2=\frac{1}{2} m v_1^2+\frac{1}{2} m v_2^2+\frac{3}{4} \times 13.6 \\
& v_{\min }=\sqrt{\frac{3 \times 13.6}{m}} \\
& K E_{\min }=\frac{1}{2} m v_{\min }^2=\frac{3}{2} \times 13.6=20.4 \mathrm{eV}
\end{aligned}$
